16:56.360 --> 17:04.820
I believe that because you have the binding problem, for example, in neuroscience, which is this classic problem of you have all these disparate pathways.

17:05.080 --> 17:13.000
You have, you know, Wernicke's area for, you know, comprehension and you have Broca's area for speech, but they're all disparate.

17:13.000 --> 17:16.460
And then we see this perceptually seamless kind of movie.

17:16.640 --> 17:18.340
And there's this question of how that is.

17:18.340 --> 17:25.940
And I think about a radio, and if you have the radio's components, you take away the battery, you take away, you know, the capacitor, you take away the antenna.

17:26.520 --> 17:30.260
Any one of those might break the radio and the music might stop playing.

